Save Our Children 
Humanitarian Awards Lunch
5/20/2023
12:00PM - 4:30PM
For the Benefit of:
Portfolio Prodigies (@portfolioprodigies)
Yacht Club Children Charity (@yachtclubchildrencharity)
Main Host: Toi Hardy (@toihardyceo)

1110 Bates Avenue
Los Angeles, CA 90029

Our dear, philanthropic friend, Toi Hardy, and her amazing friends have been working tirelessly to produce this significant charity event, and 
I am honored to serve as one of the Co-Hosts!😊🎉💯

JOIN ME AND OVER 25 HOLLYWOOD CELEBRITY NAMES FOR A RED CARPET SOCIAL DAY OF GIVING BACK. Together our efforts will provide over 1500 scholarships, meals and school supplies to at risk children nationwide. Support Our Children Humanitarian Awards recognizes individuals for their humanitarian works and efforts. With our Spirit of Giving And Leadership Humanitarian Award It's given on behalf of the children whose lives are improved by your work and our collaboration. Children who don't have access get to receive meals, school supplies, financial literacy scholarships, college scholarships & other training classes in safe environments.
Parking is at 3925 W Sunset BLVD, Los Angeles CA

I had the opportunity to sit and converse with the gent of all gents, Dr. MARTY FALLOR. It’s always a pleasure to talk to this gentleman, even more so I’m a setting like this where we dove into his philosophical outlooks for both business and life. Dr. Marty is beloved amongst all communities, and I am grateful for his continued support and friendship. If you’re not already, give @drmartyyy a follow!

“People will forget what you did, people will forget what you said, but they’ll always remember how you made them feel.” @drmayaangelou 
.
One of the golden rules @drmartyyy lives by and it has absolutely served him well. Dr. Marty, you are appreciated!
What we speak out into the universe, to others and especially ourselves, is so important. Thank you again @drmartyyy for sharing your wisdom 💎
